			<a name="research"><h3>Research</h3></a>
			<h4>Usability Improvements on iOS</h4>
			<p>
				The research phase involved investigating support tickets, analyzing dropoff rates, conducting a heuristic evaluation, and gathering feedback in order to understand pain points along the onboarding customer journey. After interviewing the sales team, implementation representatives responsible for onboarding new users, support representatives helping new customers post- setup, as well as 20 customers, it was clear that the Express Setup site caused a lot of pain both internally for stakeholders and externally for customers.
			</p>
			<img src="/images/projects/express-project/4-Quotes.png" class="image-bottom-margin">
			<p>
				From the quantitative and qualitative data collected, I discovered the following issues about the user experience:
			</p>
			<ul>
				<li>
					1) Users who had gone through the old version of Express Setup found it very long and tedious. 
				</li>
				<li>
					2) Many users were not able to complete the previous flow on their own.
				</li>
				<li>
					3) Users found the previous flow confusing.
				</li>
			</ul>
		</div>
