			<a name="results"><h3>Results</h3></a>
			
			<p>
				After the redesign, Express Setup completion increased by 10%, and users found the setup process easy. They also found the revised design cleaner, shorter, clearer and much easier to use.
			</p>

			<blockquote>“The simple, minimalist look...made it easy to understand, [it was] very helpful.”</blockquote>
			<p>-Truman, Customer</p>

			<p>
				In terms of understanding the content, users had fewer questions along the way. Feedback from users revealed that there were no longer questions pertaining to confusing content within each section, but rather, about advanced features that were omitted from Express Setup.
			</p>
			<p>
				Also, a majority of users selected the default option while completing the process. Many of these who selected “Default” at first completed the whole process once, and then returned at a later time to reconfigure and customize specific selections. Overall, participants felt confident to complete the flow on their own.
			</p>
			
			<blockquote>“It’s really good, very self-explanatory...It’s easy enough to not need an implementation representative.”</blockquote>
